					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">I'm sure someone out there has both .</div>
<br />That's not the problem. There is plenty of people who are Mega Man fans here and that knowns programming well. It's just that doing such a thing without Capcom's authorisation is completely illegal, so probably it will take a while before someone takes the risk of doing it (don't count on me). I'm confident that this will happen eventually.
<br />
<br />EDIT : Now I've watched through all stages (8 robot masters and 4 wily stages), and I admit it sounds very doable on a NES. Sure, there is some still images in cutscenes that have too much colors, and some places that would flicker. However, with minor color reduction and slight graphics changes, almost everything could be done on the real NES with a normal cartridge easily.
<br />The only exeption is that boss battle with a red core and a green core. First the cores seems to use MUCH more than 3 colors for their graphics (this can be easily scaled down). Second, there is a point where they move vertically, and are both on the same horizontal line. The only way this could be done is by making one a sprite and the other a BG, but due to their large size, as a previous guy already said, it would take almost all 64 sprites on its own. So the only real solution, without changing their attack pattern, is to use MMC5's vertical split mode (in SL mode) that only one space shooter ever used yet.</div>

					
